text.tspan: Numerical Solutions to Ordinary and Delay
Differential Equations in Chebfun
Ordinary and delay differential equations arise naturally in many applications including
mathematical biology, epidemiology, and population dynamics.
represents a general delay function.
Chebfun is an open-source package for MATLAB that overloads many built-in
functions. The resulting system allows the user to compute with functions to high
accuracy. Chebfun can solve most ODEs efficiently; however, it lacks the ability to
solve DDEs.
Matthew Meyers, Tobin Driscoll
Department of Mathematical Sciences

The Picard iteration turns this integral equation into an algorithm:
To speed up the often slow and unreliable convergence, Anderson Acceleration can
be used. Unlike a normal fixed point iteration, Anderson Acceleration uses multiple
previous iterations to optimize the next iteration.
To further assure convergence, the solve interval can be recursively shortened. The
solutions from each sub interval can then be joined back together.
